item.title: Shock death in toxic inferno case
item.description: The director of a company charged over a massive fire at a chemical factory has died, the Melbourne Magistrates Court heard on Wednesday.

item.title: Dad’s fight for life after shooting
item.description: A 37-year-old man is fighting for life after he was gunned down in a shocking broad daylight attack outside his home about 7am on Wednesday morning.

item.title: Premier defiant on 12-month restrictions
item.description: Premier Daniel Andrews is firing back at his opponents, saying he is “very hopeful” the controversial state of emergency bill will be passed in parliament despite fierce pushback from opposing politicians.

item.title: Tycoon facing ‘full force of law’
item.description: A Melbourne millionaire is facing the “full force of the law” for allegedly breaching Queensland’s strict border rules by sailing into the Gold Coast aboard his luxury superyacht.

item.title: Miner’s earnings plummet as coal price tanks
item.description: Whitehaven Coal has taken a major financial hit as tanking coal prices following the economic slump induced by the coronavirus pandemic have dented its earnings.

item.title: 6 new COVID cases in NSW
item.description: There have been six new cases of coronavirus diagnosed in NSW up to 8pm on Wednesday.

item.title: Border resident found 1000km away
item.description: A border resident has been found more than 1000 kilometres away from the strict border bubble, after Mackay police carried out a routine RBT.

item.title: Woman fined for doughnut dash
item.description: A woman who blamed a late-night doughnut craving for flouting lockdown rules received one of 156 fines dished out to Victorians over the last 24 hours.

item.title: Victoria records 149 new virus cases
item.description: Health Minister Jenny Mikakos has revealed there have been 149 new virus cases in Victoria.

item.title: ‘Cops hassled me for taking out bins’
item.description: Police have been accused of an excessive response after a Melbourne man claims officers harassed him, followed him onto his property and mentioned a “gun” when he put his bins out past curfew.
